                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">/shrug I think your logic is awful.
<br />

<br />
We can still charm solo in every zone in the game we could before. I'll still be getting an aa every 35 - 40 minutes in HoH if I want.
<br />

<br />
We're wanted in groups because we can mez, charm, slow, and even provide mana buffs when people die. Yes, it actually happens, so saying that people can get KEI from a buff whore in PoK completely ignores the fact the people die and get rezzed back all the time. By your logic, the mage gets aggro from an add and dies, so the group waits 25 minutes while he gets rezzed back, gates to PoK, hopefully has an enchanter there casting, and then runs back through 5 zones to the group.
<br />

<br />
In addition, I've never gotten why people say that things like mez, charm, haste, and slow are useless because other classes can do them as well. Uh, yeah, but we can do them all. Ever hear of a shaman not LFG? No bard to be found? No beastlord around? (ok, the no beastlord thing is pushing it - they're like friggin' rabbits <img src="images/smiles/icon_wink.gif" alt="icon_wink.gif" border="0" />)
<br />

<br />
The enchanter class will *always* be welcome in groups because we provide a nice buffer for thos OH SHIT situations where a group would die otherwise, we can do some dps, we can refresh a haste w/ attack buff when it drops, we can slow, yadda yadda yadda.
<br />

<br />
As for raiding ... /shrug. I'm sure there will still be a reason for enchanters in a bunch of raids, and there will probably be some events where we're 5th class nukers. Such is the way of EQ, and almost every class has to deal with this to one extent or another.
<br />

<br />
Your final thought I agree with, however. Sony really has done a friggin' awful PR job. Not much to do about that.
<br />

<br />
In fact, I'd be truly shocked if Brenlo has even come to the runes in the past 6 months, so the chances of him seeing this point are about nil and zero.
<br />

<br />
To sum up - I don't agree with you. Enchanters are, in my opinion, in a very good place in the game. In addition, it's too early to tell how things will be in OoW. Post again in 6 weeks, and if I decide to purchase OoW, I'll might be more willing to support you.
<br />

<br />
For now, I think you're wrong.</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br />It's easy to use - if you're one of the 2% of the population who thinks logically and can read an instruction manual. The other 98% of the population would find it very hard or impossible to use.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
