                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I know its very early in the expansion for me to eulogise about it too much, but its also too early to be totally negative.
<br />

<br />
Today, in OoW i had the BEST day grouping since i started playing EQ..flat out no questions.
<br />

<br />
I was in Ruined City of Dranik, we had a wander round killed a few mobs.  Every time we pulled we were almost guarnteed a minimum of 1 add, obviously cant pacify as dont have the spells.  Roamers were abundant and we couldn't find any spots that were safe at all, roamers moved quickly in some cases so needed good reactions, other times they were visible easily coming towards camp and i could CC out of camp.
<br />

<br />
If they reached us, the hits were small enough that a resist didnt flatten me instantly, but fast enough that it was an issue, at most times we had 2-4 mobs in camp, nto through bad pulling or bad management, just through how the zone was designed.
<br />

<br />
Then another group of guildys said hey lets try this named, took us a few trys but we dropped him, had some nasty ae mana drain, needed a bit of work to work out what to do, btu we got him down.
<br />

<br />
We wandered around some more, found a roaming named and got 7 adds roamed into us during the fight and clear up, a few resisted mezzes didn't mean i died, i coudl happily take the hits of a couple of mobs at atime, it needed an alert cleric to do it and most of my AA tools to survive but there wasnt any ridiculous 1 roundign like you see so often in GoD.
<br />

<br />
Then we wandered off to anothr area where we camped for a while, foudn a few named PH, got a few named, 3 spell runes for ourselves and a good chunk of exp, most areas were next to impossible to single pull and no real safe spots existed to easily set up camp without the danger of roaming adds on reasnably fast respawns.
<br />

<br />
I'm not too happy about the nerf to charm, but if thats the price to pay for well thought out zones, zones that are a pleasure to look at and explore, where i actually care whats round the corner cos its nto the same as the 1000 other corners i just been round.  Where mobs dont instantly kill me on a mez resist, yet still provide a challenge. Where i can actually go back to the role i made my enc for, to bring order to the chaos of lots fo adds, to actually be able to cc.  
<br />

<br />
Thats a price i'm willing to pay</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=673380" target="_blank" class="postlink"><img src="http://www.mithrilweb.com/sigs/Tidemini.jpg" border="0" /> </a>
<br />
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=673380" target="_blank" class="postlink">Qujam</a>-Bedazzler-<a href="http://www.tunare-europa.co.uk/tide/news/news.php" target="_blank" class="postlink">Tide</a>
