                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">On test there is a -resist focus that could be for our epic.  If so, this could be why the mobs are resiting mez so much: when we have our epic, the mobs will resist an acceptable amount.  =/
<br />

<br />
I like the idea of capping mob DPS while charmed.  I don't like the idea of the mob's DPS while uncharmed being orders of magnatude more than while charmed.
<br />

<br />
We are far too fragile for our job.  Now we have a bunch of AAs that should help, but all of them have long reuse timers.  Once we run out of "get out of jail free" cards we are helpless.
<br />

<br />
The reason why enchanters ask for FM is because it is a "get out of jail free" card that <span style="font-weight: bold">isn't</span> tied to a reuse timer.  It is tied to a renewable resource, and has a cost, but you don't die just because you ran into a second emergency before some silly timer reset.  I don't want FM.  I want an ability that consumes resources that lets us deal with being the only player with a significant amount of hate on a mob, one that isn't on a timer.
<br />

<br />
We had this pre-55.  Memorize 2 stuns (resource cost: spell gems and casting time), and you almost always had the ability to buy yourself time to use your other abilities.  With PoP and GoD mob DPS has inflated to the point that we can't survive the casting time of our spells, so they have gone by the wayside.  And OoW's huge mob resist rate has done the same thing, together with our barren selection of defence spells.
<br />

<br />
I want to be a class that gets aggro and doesn't die.
<br />
I want to have options when it happens.
<br />
I enjoy the mental rush of charm, just keep the DPS on mob and on player during break balanced and I'm happy.
<br />
Let my buffs be superceded (BST mana regen -- admittedly, you rolled back paragon2.0, Shaman melee buffs -- haste cap and a total of +15% damage modifier makes SoS's change over SoV look cosmetic), I don't mind.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
