                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Chin up mate, we arent useless by a long shot. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
The charm change can be more than just a 50% dps reduction btw, I was running around with a mountain baku (sp?), which is a large rancor looking mob, utterly ace btw.  It hits for 240 charmed, 689 uncharmed. 
<br />
On the other hand the glider things hit for 490 ish uncharmed, and 225 charmed.
<br />

<br />
I managed to run around with this thing charmed, as well as deal with adds, and slow, and debuff, for nearly 2 hours before I ran out of mana.  Granted im an EP ench with a spattering of VT gear.
<br />
Charm seems to be slightly more reliable, and the mobs seem to have a slightly higher miss rate than normal too.
<br />

<br />
Didnt use snare, just WoM (without mez mastery), and the clr stunned it for me a few seconds after WoM landed.  Gave me more than enough time to retash and recharm.  Had a few scary moments, but I trust my guildie healers. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Was hitting around 200 dps with just the pet, which is rather good dps considering I was also the slower and CC. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
A bard *can* run around the mob till he mezzes it, but then most if not all the songs drop while he/she runs around spamming the mob with mez.
<br />

<br />
Depends on your style tho, personally I have a pet up as much as possable, but my true love is crowd control, and the current setup of the zones means adds are a given, mnk / bard puller or not. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
Edit :  Almost forgot, as for raids......
<br />

<br />
Offtanking in guild is a typical thing, my guild had a problem with it for a long time (from the ench point of view), but it got sorted a while ago.
<br />

<br />
Now we still have offtanking, depending on the number of ench, but generally. the offtanks only use incite / spells to hold the add long enough for us to mez.  
<br />
Still get the odd mez break, mainly from the knights who dont seem to pay attention sometimes, but we'v got the guild leaders backing about stuff being mezzed. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Lack of use on your raids isnt a class issue, its a guild issue. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=499750" target="_blank" class="postlink">Thandor lv 68 Wanna'be Gnome Coercer</a>
