                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Charm is not the be-all and end-all of being an enchanter.
<br />
Not for me. Not for a lot of people.
<br />
No, I don't like how it works now. It needs adjusting.
<br />

<br />
What I DO want back is the feeling of contributing something other than buffs when we go to places that have mobs above my level.
<br />
I was grouping in Muramite. I could not mez a thing. (Level restriction) I CC'd with root.
<br />
Well you don't need an enchie to do that, do you?
<br />
Until I get my first mez at lvl 67 - and I've so far managed to get ONE rune total in 2 days of grouping and taking down various nameds - which gave me lvl 66 Ethereal Rune.
<br />
That's dandy.
<br />
So by the time I hit 68 I might get another one. If the TANK doesn't win it.
<br />
I do not begrudge anyone a rune for anything, but without those spells I'm useless to my group since I don't add DPS, I cannot CC any better than the wizard - who can at least snare - or the shammy or anyone else for that matter, since I'm stuck with rooting things if they happen to be above the level cap of Bliss. Which in there is *everything*. So even at lvl 70 I cannot mez them if I don't have the higher spells. 
<br />
That's what I want fixed. The droprate of runes that I have seen is bloody well atrocious - and then you fight over them with every other class in creation, including the tanks.
<br />
Until I can do my CC job there, I'm a buffbot in those zones, nothing more. But to get those runes I need to group there. 
<br />

<br />
On the upside, Bliss sticks nearly every time in Walls and other places without the need of tash first. I locked down 5 yellows in Walls of Slaughter without having to tash any of them. If I'd had to, my group would have wiped.
<br />
I *would* like to thank Sony for that little bit of good news.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
