		<td width="150" align="left" valign="top" class="row1"><a name="69484"></a><span class="name"><span class="usercolor">Unmei</span></span><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_offline.gif" border="0" align="absbottom" alt="Offline" title="Offline" /><div class="gensmall"><img src="images/ranks/rank_supporter.gif" alt="<b><center><font color=orange>Site Supporter</font></b></center>" title="<b><center><font color=orange>Site Supporter</font></b></center>" border="0" /><br /><b><center><font color=orange>Site Supporter</font></b></center></div><div align="center"><img src="http://users.dhp.com/~mpureka/avatar.jpg" alt="Avatar" border="0" /></div><br /><div align="left" class="gensmall">Joined:&nbsp;27 Aug 2003</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Total posts:&nbsp;2135</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Location:&nbsp;Planet Yuggoth</div><div align="left" class="gensmall">Gender:&nbsp;Unknown</div></td>
                <td class="row1" width="100%" height="28" valign="top"><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tr>
                                <td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td><a href="viewtopic.php?p=69484#69484"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails">Posted: Thu Sep 16, 2004 11:53 am<span class="gen">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp; &nbsp;Post subject: </span></td>
                                <td align="right" valign="top" nowrap="nowrap"><a href="posting.php?mode=quote&amp;p=69484"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/lang_english/icon_quote.gif" alt="Reply with quote" title="Reply with quote" border="0" /></a>    </td></tr></table></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I've messed around a bit and didn't have ANY trouble mezzing ANYTHING in the zones I explored. (City of Dranik, Bloodfields, Harbinger's Spire, Dranik Hollows expeditions, Noble's Causeway) - I don't know where these reports of high resists are coming from, because several people in THIS thread have stated that Wall of Slaughter is relatively low resist, and Muramite Proving Grounds mostly contains mobs that are too high of level to mez until you have the 67(?) mez spell.
<br />

<br />
So I don't see any basis for a "They raised resists on mobs just so they could put a resist mod on our epic."  I see no signs of increased resist rate.  In fact, I was going to comment that most of the stuff I've tangled with so far seemed really LIGHT on the resistance.  
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">What if charmed mobs conitinued their lower dps output for a brief time, but an ex-charm pet provides no experience (or almost none) for several minutes after it breaks? It would solve the reverse charm issue that I assume SOE will consider an exploit of the game mechanics. You would have a vested interest in continuing with the same pet, you have a better chance of surviving a pet break, but you still have to be on your toes.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
This isn't a bad idea, but actually, I'm sortof in the reverse camp on one issue - I _don't_ think we should be encouraged to run around with the same pet all the time.   I think that's part of the problem here.  Running around with the same pet all the time and recasting charm every 7.5 minutes is what got us into this mess in the first place.   So I'd like to see either the "mob does reduced damage after charm break for 30(?) seconds or until it takes damage" route, or, alternatively (really 'radical' idea here) - make charm FIXED duration (Maybe even nudge the duration down a bit - 5 minutes instead of 7.5).   And have it leave a duration buff on the mob for 7.5 minutes after that that makes it impossible to RECHARM that same target.  Yes, this is approaching "dictate" style charms, but I think that's fine, because the problems I see with Dictate style charm is: #1: Mana cost is too high. #2: Recast time is too long. #3: Duration is too short.   A little bit of adjusting, and you have a charm that can be used as an "in fight" CC tool, but that doesn't give us the equivalent "Suuuupah mage pet!" that we run around with all the time.
<br />

<br />
Either way though, I'm firmly of the opinion that the 30% charm XP penalty needs to GO AWAY NOW.   At LEAST in the OoW zones.  I'm relatively okay with contributing less DPS as long as I don't steal XP to do it.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
