                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I agree with you Unmei about the idea of turning over charm pets. In an ideal setting I think of a pull with several mobs, you mez one, charm another and use it to help you control that pull.  Eventually you clean up the mobs down to charmed ones, then charm breaks and you kill those.
<br />

<br />
I see nothing wrong at all with a charm system that forces you to turn over pets, except this is exactly what many people do in HoH and it seems to be the basis of the reverse charm idea.
<br />

<br />
Issues I see with charm in general are that you can break charm, mez, blur a mob and have it do massive healing in a short time. Excharm mobs shouldn't do this right away, perhaps after a minute or two, or perhaps they should never really forget you exist until they die or you zone (so they never regen).
<br />

<br />
If you use a mob to burn down a charm pet, perhaps that mob that did all your work should remember its efforts, and keep taking the experience when the excharm pet dies. Its odd that you would get the kill experience from doing only 3% damage to a mob. If I was the mob killing the charm pet, I would be pissed off if I didn't get the exp.  <img src="images/smiles/icon_razz.gif" alt="icon_razz.gif" border="0" />  It kinda makes all enchanters into the wandering guards in greater fay who KS a whole kill just because they took out the last hp.</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
                </table></td>
        </tr>
